---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const updated = "April 25, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Service — Dualio"
  description="The rules for using Dualio during private beta."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="container legal section">
    <span class="eyebrow">Last updated · {updated}</span>
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>

    <p>
      These terms apply to the Dualio mobile app and the dualio.app website
      while Dualio is in private beta.
    </p>

    <h2>Beta nature</h2>
    <p>
      Dualio is early software. Things may break, data may occasionally need
      to be migrated, and features may change without notice. Don't store your
      only copy of anything important here.
    </p>

    <h2>Your content</h2>
    <p>
      You keep ownership of everything you save into Dualio. We process your
      content only to make it searchable and useful for you. We need a license
      to do that processing — to read, store, generate metadata for, and
      display your content back to you across your devices. That license
      ends when you delete an item or your account.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Don't use Dualio to break the law.</li>
      <li>Don't upload content you don't have the right to save.</li>
      <li>
        Don't try to extract data from other users, abuse the AI processing
        pipeline, or interfere with the service.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Free tier limits</h2>
    <p>
      During beta the free tier is generous but not unlimited. Limits exist on
      the number of saved items, image uploads, AI processing attempts, and
      original-image retention. Limits are enforced server-side and may be
      adjusted as we learn what users actually need.
    </p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>
      Dualio is provided as-is. We are not liable for lost data, missed
      reminders, or any indirect damages arising from your use of the service.
      Where required by law, this limit does not apply to gross negligence.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms. If we change anything material, we will
      notify users by email or in-app before the change takes effect.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:hello@dualio.app">hello@dualio.app</a>
    </p>

    <p class="muted small">
      Working draft — finalised wording will replace this before public
      launch.
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .legal h2 {
    margin-top: 2em;
  }

  .legal ul {
    padding-left: 1.25em;
    margin: 0 0 1em;
  }

  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5em;
  }

  .small {
    font-size: 13px;
    margin-top: 3em;
  }
</style>
